The paper deals with the analysis of the ergodic capacity of a MIMO dual-hop relay channel, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of random matrix theory also suggests a potential fit for the statistical theory (cs.ST) sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of system and channel characteristics, which could be relevant to the communication (cs.COMM) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA) sub-categories.
